===聖禮===
信義宗認為上帝藉「施恩的工具」給與罪人一切的屬靈福分，施恩具就是聖經裡的福音信息和兩種[[聖禮|聖禮]]：洗禮和聖餐。路德教會認聖禮就是上帝的話語與外在媒介聯繫起來，藉此建立、加強信心，使領受的人罪得赦免。1530年《奧斯堡信條》第五條指出：

{{quotation|因為藉著道和聖禮，好比工具一樣，就有聖靈賜給人；祂隨時隨地照上帝所喜悅的，在聽福音之人的心裏生出信來；這信，就是說，上帝非因我們自己的功勞，乃因基督的緣故，稱那凡相信因基督的緣故得蒙恩寵的人為義。<ref>[http://bookofconcord.org/augsburgconfession.php#article5 Article V. Of the Ministry] {{Wayback|url=http://bookofconcord.org/augsburgconfession.php#article5 |date=20110810073345 }}, The Augsburg Confession</ref>}}

====洗禮====
路德教會認為聖靈藉洗禮這聖禮，向罪人賜下福音，給他們重生（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/提多書|提多書3:5]]）、除去他們一切的罪（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/使徒行傳|使徒行傳2:38]]）。路德教會相信，當主耶穌應許「信而受洗的必然得救」（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/馬可福音|馬可福音16:16]]）的時候，已清楚地指出這是洗禮帶來的福分。路德會相信洗禮是耶穌為所有人設立的（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/馬太福音|馬太福音28:19]]），當中包括嬰孩（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/使徒行傳|使徒行傳2:37-39]]）。教會認為嬰孩和成人都是生而有罪（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/約翰福音|約翰福音3:6]]），都需要重生，也都應該藉着洗禮得到信心（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/約翰福音|約翰福音3:5]]）。<ref>[http://www.wels.net/what-we-believe/statements-beliefs/this-we-believe/means-grace This We Believe - The Means of Grace] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wels.net/what-we-believe/statements-beliefs/this-we-believe/means-grace |date=20150507125913 }}: "We believe that the blessing of Baptism is meant for all people (Matthew 28:19), including infants. Infants are born sinful (John 3:6) and therefore need to be born again, that is, to be brought to faith, through Baptism (John 3:5)...We reject the view that babies should not be baptized and that they cannot believe in Christ (Luke 18:15-17)"</ref>

====聖餐====
路德宗教會相信所有參與聖餐的人在領受餅和酒時，同時領受主的真身體及真寶血–「基督在沒有改變的餅與酒之內，與餅和酒同在，在餅和酒之下」(in, with and under the bread and wine)（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/哥林多前書|哥林多前書10:16]]）。路德教會堅信，當信徒領受主的真身體和真寶血時，他們也同時得到罪的赦免（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/馬太福音|馬太福音26:28]]），但未認罪的信徒、非信徒和拒絕承認基督真身體臨在於聖餐的人，若領受基督的身體和寶血，只會令他們被定罪：<ref>[http://www.wels.net/what-we-believe/statements-beliefs/this-we-believe/means-grace This We Believe - The Means of Grace] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wels.net/what-we-believe/statements-beliefs/this-we-believe/means-grace |date=20150507125913 }}: "We believe that all who join in the Sacrament of the Lord's Supper receive the true body and blood of Christ in, with, and under the bread and wine (1 Corinthians 10:16)...We believe that Christ's words of institution cause the real presence—not any human action. As believers receive his body and blood, they also receive the forgiveness of sins (Matthew 26:28) and the comfort and assurance that they are truly his own. Unbelievers also receive Christ's body and blood, but to their judgment (1 Corinthians 11:29)...Scripture teaches that all communicants receive both the bread and wine and the body and blood of Christ (1 Corinthians 10:16)."</ref><ref>WELS Topical Q&A: [https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20090927092424/https://www.wels.net/cgi-bin/site.pl?1518&cuTopic_topicID=57&cuItem_itemID=27701 Who may Commune/Serve? - Closed Communion], "Communion is based on faith in Christ, so non-Christians cannot attend. Communion is for forgiveness so the impenitent who are living in a sin cannot attend. Communion calls for self-examination so the uninstructed cannot attend, even our own children. If communicants do not recognize the presence of Christ's body and blood in the sacrament, they receive it not to their blessing but to their condemnation, so members of churches that do not believe in the real presence cannot attend with us."</ref>
{{quotation|無論何人，不按理吃主的餅、喝主的杯，就是干犯主的身、主的血了。人應當自己省察，然後吃這餅、喝這杯。因為人吃喝，若不分辨是主的身體，就是吃喝自己的罪了。|{{cuv|哥林多後書|11|27|29}}<ref>WELS Topical Q&A: [https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20090927184709/https://www.wels.net/cgi-bin/site.pl?1518&cuTopic_topicID=58&cuItem_itemID=12174 Real Presence – Holy Communion]</ref>}}

===預定論===
信義宗教會強調，在創世之前，上帝已經{{link-en|揀選|Predestination#In_Lutheranism}}了誰人可「在適當的時候藉福音得救」，「並保守他們在信裏(Preservation of faith)直至得到永生（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/羅馬書|羅馬書8:29,30]]）」，但與[[歸正宗|歸正宗]]教會不同，信義宗教會並不認為上帝[[預選說|預選]]或揀選誰人受永遠懲罰（「預定受罰」），因為《[[聖經|聖經]]》亦清楚指出，上帝願意所有人得救（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/提摩太前書|提摩太前書2:4]]；[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/彼得後書|彼得後書3:9]]）<ref>[http://www.wels.net/what-we-believe/statements-beliefs/this-we-believe/justification This We Believe - Justification By Grace through Faith] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wels.net/what-we-believe/statements-beliefs/this-we-believe/justification |date=20150215132555 }}: "We believe that already before the world was created, God chose those individuals whom he would in time convert through the gospel of Christ and preserve in faith to eternal life (Ephesians 1:4-6; Romans 8:29,30)."</ref><ref>[http://www.wels.net/what-we-believe/statements-beliefs/this-we-believe/justification?page=0,1 This We Believe - Justification By Grace through Faith] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wels.net/what-we-believe/statements-beliefs/this-we-believe/justification?page=0,1 |date=20150228150018 }}: "We reject the false and blasphemous conclusion that those who are lost were predestined, or elected, by God to damnation, for God wants all people to be saved (1 Timothy 2:4; 2 Peter 3:9)."</ref><ref>Epitome of the Formula of Concord (協同信條), [http://bookofconcord.org/fc-ep.php#part11.21 XI. Election: Negative These-False Doctrine concerning This Article] {{Wayback|url=http://bookofconcord.org/fc-ep.php#part11.21 |date=20201031063041 }}, 1517</ref>

===末世論===
有別於很多新教宗派，信義宗並不認同「千禧論」，即一些聲稱耶穌基督會在地上統治一個有形國度的[[千禧年|千禧年]]說法。路德教會認為「千禧論」，不論[[千禧年前论|千禧年前論]]抑或[[千禧年后论|千禧年後論]]，都沒有充分聖經根據，更認為這學說錯誤地引導信徒把期望建立在一個地上的政治國度之上。（[[Wikisource:zh:聖經_(和合本)/約翰福音|約翰福音18:36]]）<ref>The Eternal Word: A Lutheran Confession for the Twenty-First Century, [http://celc.info/home/180010197/180010197/files/CELC_Article_V.pdf Article V - Eagerly await the Savior: The Doctrine of the Last Things (Eschatology)] {{Wayback|url=http://celc.info/home/180010197/180010197/files/CELC_Article_V.pdf |date=20150212192429 }}, pp11-21</ref><ref>[http://www.wels.net/what-we-believe/statements-beliefs/this-we-believe/jesus-return This We Believe - Jesus' Return and the Judgment] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wels.net/what-we-believe/statements-beliefs/this-we-believe/jesus-return |date=20150507175031 }}: "We reject the teaching that Christ will reign on earth for a thousand years in a physical, earthly kingdom. This teaching (millennialism) has no valid scriptural basis and falsely leads Christians to set their hopes upon an earthly kingdom of Christ (John 18:36)." )</ref>

