=== 台灣信義宗教會 ===
{{Main|台灣信義宗}}信義宗於1950年代在台宣教初期，即有四國（[[美國|美國]]、[[挪威|挪威]]、[[丹麥|丹麥]]、[[芬蘭|芬蘭]]）八差會一起合作。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=台灣信義宗|url=https://zh.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=%E5%8F%B0%E7%81%A3%E4%BF%A1%E7%BE%A9%E5%AE%97&oldid=44495733|date=2017-05-25|journal=维基百科，自由的百科全书|language=zh|access-date=2019-12-01|archive-date=2020-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201102174153/https://zh.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=%E5%8F%B0%E7%81%A3%E4%BF%A1%E7%BE%A9%E5%AE%97&oldid=44495733|dead-url=no}}</ref>

多國差因政策等原因已不再教會裡，大多信義宗教會會各自獨立發展，漸漸形成新的總會。

目前在台灣的信義宗教會，共有六個總會如下︰

* [[基督教台灣信義會|基督教台灣信義會]]：成立於1954年，在全台各縣市均有分堂。其母會為丹麥差會、挪威差會以及美國福音路德會。

* [[中華信義會|中華基督教信義會（中國基督教信義會）]]：成立於西元1958年，先在[[桃竹苗|桃竹苗地區]]，後向[[臺北都會區|臺北都會區]]工作。由北美路德信友教會捐助成立。
* 臺灣中國基督教信義會：成立於1960年，在[[臺北都會區|臺北都會區]]、[[宜蘭縣|宜蘭縣]]、[[桃園市|桃園市]]工作。由挪威信義差會設立。

* 中華基督教福音信義會：成立於1973年，在中部地區（[[臺中市|臺中市]]）工作。由挪威福音信義教會設立。

* 中華民國台灣基督教信義會：成立於1977年，先在[[屏東縣|屏東縣]]，後在[[高雄市|高雄市]]、[[臺北都會區|臺北都會區]]、[[新竹市|新竹市]]工作。設有「沐恩之家」，從事福音戒毒；現由路加傳道會管理。由芬蘭差會（Finnish Evangelical Lutheran Mission）捐助成立。
* 中華福音道路德會：由美國密蘇里州路德會之差會創建，自1951年開始工作起，即獨自發展。在[[嘉義縣|嘉義縣]]成立的「[[嘉義縣私立協同高級中學|協同中學]]」，為少數基督教中學之一。

==教徒数目==
全球信义宗教會約有8000萬至1億信徒。<ref>[http://www.trinitylonglake.org/page_to_print.cfm?id=430 Our Patron - Martin Luther] {{Wayback|url=http://www.trinitylonglake.org/page_to_print.cfm?id=430 |date=20141026172831 }}, Trinity Lutheran Church, 2013</ref>这里的统计，包括了所有名义上的信义宗教徒，他们不一定归属于某个具体的教会。信義宗現時是[[芬兰|芬蘭]]、[[挪威|挪威]]、[[丹麦|丹麥]]及[[冰岛|冰島]]的[[國教|國教]]。2000年之前，信義宗亦是[[瑞典|瑞典]]的[[國教|國教]]，但其後瑞典修法，取消了信義宗在瑞典的國教地位。

==合一運動==
世界信義宗聯會及[[天主教會|羅馬天主教]]自1965年成立了工作小組嘗試修補兩教派間的宗教裂痕及展開對話。及至1997年2月，世界信義宗聯會與天主教會發表《[[关于称义教义的联合声明|关于称义教义的联合声明]]》，惟雙方仍存在分歧，聲明亦未得到[[天主教教廷|天主教教廷]]的認可<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cmacuhk.org.hk/version3/mag/mag_letter_14/mag_letter_14b.htm|title=從宣道會看基督教與天主教的異同|accessdate=2017-11-07|author=|date=|work=|publisher=基督教宣道會香港區聯會|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110128024537/http://www.cmacuhk.org.hk/version3/mag/mag_letter_14/mag_letter_14b.htm|archive-date=2011-01-28|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。在1999年10月31日，雙方在[[德国|德國]][[奥格斯堡|奧格斯堡]]簽署文件確認《关于称义教义的联合声明》（Joint Declaration on the Doctrine of Justification）<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://christiantimes.org.hk/Common/Reader/News/ShowNews.jsp?Cid=323&Pid=21&Version=0&Charset=big5_hkscs&Nid=6241|title=信義宗與梵蒂岡簽締《因信稱義聯合聲明》|accessdate=2017-11-07|author=|date=1999-10-10|work=|publisher=時代論壇|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109070025/https://christiantimes.org.hk/Common/Reader/News/ShowNews.jsp?Cid=323&Pid=21&Version=0&Charset=big5_hkscs&Nid=6241|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[循道宗|循道宗]]亦肯定兩教會共同簽署的聯合聲明，於2006年7月23日於[[大韩民国|南韓]][[首爾|首爾]]加入聯署有關聲明<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://china.ucanews.com/2006/08/04/KO00774/|title=世界衛理宗議會加入天主教與信義宗的《成義信理聯合聲明》|author=|date=2006-08-04|work=天亞社中文網|newspaper=|accessdate=2017-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107165253/http://china.ucanews.com/2006/08/04/KO00774/|archive-date=2017-11-07|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，並附上一份循道衛理宗教會對「稱義」的理解文件，兩份文件的中文譯本亦已於2014年5月24日於香港循道衛理聯合教會九龍堂，由三方教會簽署領袖確認。<ref>[http://www.methodist.org.hk/media/activity/2014/05/23/S140525-JDDJ.pdf 信義宗教會與天主教會有關稱義的聯合聲明 世界循道衞理宗協會就有關稱義教義聯合聲明的聲明 互認中文譯本簽署典禮] {{Wayback|url=http://www.methodist.org.hk/media/activity/2014/05/23/S140525-JDDJ.pdf |date=20200801001010 }}，循道衛理聯合教會，2014-05-23</ref>

至於另外兩大國際信義宗合一組織，包括[[國際路德會|國際路德會]]與[[世界路德宗認信聯會|世界路德宗認信聯會]]，則對《因信稱義聯合聲明》普遍持否定態度，認為簽署雙方在信仰最核心的「救恩」問題上，依然各說各話<ref>[http://ncronline.org/blogs/all-things-catholic/german-pope-heads-land-luther A German pope heads for the Land of Luther] {{Wayback|url=http://ncronline.org/blogs/all-things-catholic/german-pope-heads-land-luther |date=20201107181718 }}, {{link-en|National Catholic Reporter|National Catholic Reporter}}, 2 Sept 2011 {{en}}, saying "To be sure, the Joint Declaration has not exactly brought about an ecumenical New Jerusalem. Some Lutherans have rejected the agreement, including the International Lutheran Council and the Confessional Evangelical Lutheran Conference. On the Catholic side, the Vatican’s approval remains officially binding, but enthusiasm varies."</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.lcms.org/Document.fdoc?src=lcm&id=339 |title=The Joint Declaration on the Doctrine of Justiﬁcation in Confessional Lutheran Perspective |accessdate=2015-02-13 |archive-date=2020-08-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801001020/https://www.lcms.org/Document.fdoc?src=lcm&id=339 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=mccain>{{cite news| url=http://firstthings.com/blogs/evangel/2010/03/a-betrayal-of-the-gospel-the-joint-declaration-on-the-doctrine-of-justification/| title=A Betrayal of the Gospel: The Joint Declaration on the Doctrine of Justification| last=McCain| first=Rev. Paul T.| date=12 March 2010| work=First Things| issn=1047-5141| accessdate=2014-01-17| archive-date=2013-09-13| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130913031500/http://firstthings.com/blogs/evangel/2010/03/a-betrayal-of-the-gospel-the-joint-declaration-on-the-doctrine-of-justification/| dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="WELS-JDDJ">{{cite web|url=https://www.wels.net/cgi-bin/site.pl?1518&cuTopic_topicID=19&cuItem_itemID=6741|title=WELS Topical Q&A - Justification|accessdate=2017-11-07|author=|date=|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090927135957/https://www.wels.net/cgi-bin/site.pl?1518&cuTopic_topicID=19&cuItem_itemID=6741|archivedate=2009-09-27|quote=The biblical Lutheran teaching of “forensic” justification maintains that the only effective cause of our forgiveness is a verdict of God that takes place outside of ourselves. We are declared “not guilty” entirely on the basis of what Christ has done for us. Catholic teaching on justification makes a change within man part of the cause of our forgiveness. The Joint Declaration does not represent a change in the teachings of the Roman Catholic Church. It does nothing to repudiate Rome’s historic position on the doctrine. The Joint Declaration is nothing more than an ambiguous statement, carefully worded to make it possible for the Pope’s representatives to sign it without changing, retracting, or correcting anything that has been taught by the Roman Catholic Church since the time of the Council of Trent in the sixteenth century. The Joint Declaration is a compromise. It masquerades as a significant change which brings Roman Catholicism in line with confessional Lutheranism on the teaching of justification. In fact, it is a deception that presents the appearance of agreement without any real substance that would make agreement possible. It is a thinly veiled attempt on the part of ecumenicism to embrace Catholicism. In the final analysis it appears that Rome has moved closer to reattaching what was lost in the sixteenth century without any substantive change in its doctrinal position.|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wels.net/news-events/forward-in-christ/october-1999/question-indulgences-again|title=A Question of Indulgences - Again|accessdate=2017-11-07|author=Joel Gerlach|date=|work=WELS|publisher=|language=en-US|archive-date=2014-06-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140606224648/http://www.wels.net/news-events/forward-in-christ/october-1999/question-indulgences-again|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

